Introduction

Yoon San Ha is a South Korean singer and actor under Fantagio. He is widely recognized as the maknae and lead vocalist of the boy group ASTRO and its first-ever sub-unit Moonbin & Sanha.

Sanha participated in the second Fantagio iTeen audition, showcasing his singing and guitar skills. He joined Fantagio as a trainee on December 16, 2012, and was later officially introduced through the Fantagio iTeen Photo Test Cut on February 4, 2014.

He debuted as the youngest member of ASTRO on February 23, 2016, with the album "Spring Up". Additionally, Sanha debuted in the sub-unit Moonbin & Sanha alongside fellow member Moonbin on September 14, 2020, with their first extended play "In-Out".
